# Trivy ignore list — base-image CVEs fixed upstream in Debian 12 but not yet
# rebuilt into gcr.io/distroless/python3-debian12:nonroot. Re-evaluate every
# Monday; remove entries once `docker pull gcr.io/distroless/python3-debian12:nonroot`
# returns a new digest and Trivy reports clean.
#
# All entries below are non-exploitable in this container because:
#   - The MCP server is a stdio child process with no network listener.
#   - It does not parse untrusted tar archives, does not run http.client
#     servers, and does not handle email headers.
#   - libc6 memalign integer overflow requires hostile local code; the
#     container runs only our pinned Python entrypoint as nonroot.
#   - the libssl3 PKCS7_verify use-after-free requires the app to verify a
#     crafted PKCS#7/S-MIME signed message; this server only opens outbound
#     TLS to Atlassian and never calls PKCS7_verify, so the affected code
#     path is unreachable.
#
# Review-by: 2026-06-15

# libc6 — glibc memalign integer overflow (fixed in 2.36-9+deb12u14)
CVE-2026-0861

# libssl3 — OpenSSL PKCS7_verify() heap use-after-free (fixed in 3.0.20-1~deb12u2).
# TEMPORARY: as of 2026-06-12 the pinned distroless :nonroot digest still ships
# 3.0.19-1~deb12u2, and `docker pull gcr.io/distroless/python3-debian12:nonroot`
# resolves to the same digest (no patched rebuild published yet). Remove this
# entry and refresh the Dockerfile base digest once distroless ships 3.0.20.
CVE-2026-45447

# cpython — http.client read-buffer DoS (fixed in 3.11.2-6+deb12u7)
CVE-2025-13836

# cpython — tarfile infinite loop (fixed in 3.11.2-6+deb12u7)
CVE-2025-8194

# cpython — email header injection via unquoted newlines (fixed in 3.11.2-6+deb12u7)
CVE-2026-1299
